<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1435,861,1012]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,903,929]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; empodium entire; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[947,971,903,928]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">sc</emphasis>
) ahead of rear shield margin, directed posteriorly; paraxial tibial seta (
<emphasis box="[525,543,945,970]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">l’</emphasis>
) absent; coxae I and coxae II each with 3 setae.
</paragraph>
